[{"text": "Obsessive Compulsive Disorder (OCD) - Part 1", "start": 0.0, "duration": 3.4}, {"text": "There are popular posts on social media that say,", "start": 3.4, "duration": 2.9}, {"text": "if you have problems with the minor mistakes\nin these pictures,", "start": 6.3, "duration": 3.03}, {"text": "then you have OCD.", "start": 9.33, "duration": 1.37}, {"text": "After looking at the pictures,", "start": 10.88, "duration": 1.75}, {"text": "you feel disturbed", "start": 12.63, "duration": 1.03}, {"text": "and think that maybe you have OCD after all.", "start": 13.66, "duration": 2.64}, {"text": "What exactly is OCD?", "start": 16.3, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Is it really that simple to diagnose?", "start": 18.3, "duration": 2.23}, {"text": "Obsessive compulsive disorder or OCD", "start": 20.74, "duration": 3.06}, {"text": "is a mental disorder.", "start": 23.8, "duration": 1.46}, {"text": "It starts with an obsession", "start": 25.56, "duration": 1.54}, {"text": "which is the unwanted,", "start": 27.1, "duration": 1.4}, {"text": "and disturbing thoughts or images", "start": 28.5, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that are intrusive and reoccuring.", "start": 30.5, "duration": 1.7}, {"text": "To calm themselves with the obsession,", "start": 32.2, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the patient makes a certain compulsion,", "start": 34.2, "duration": 2.16}, {"text": "repetitive actions or behaviors", "start": 36.36, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that are done excessively", "start": 38.36, "duration": 1.3}, {"text": "and may not be related to the obsession.", "start": 39.76, "duration": 2.22}, {"text": "Some scientists grouped OCD", "start": 42.24, "duration": 2.02}, {"text": "based on their main obsession.", "start": 44.26, "duration": 1.54}, {"text": "The classifications are", "start": 46.04, "duration": 1.39}, {"text": "One:", "start": 47.43, "duration": 0.5}, {"text": "Obsession to contamination", "start": 48.26, "duration": 1.67}, {"text": "Everyone with this type of OCD", "start": 50.36, "duration": 1.9}, {"text": "has an obsession that bacteria might infect them", "start": 52.26, "duration": 2.5}, {"text": "or their family,", "start": 54.76, "duration": 0.94}, {"text": "known as mysophobia or germophobia.", "start": 55.9, "duration": 2.73}, {"text": "So they wash their hands every 5 minutes or so,", "start": 59.08, "duration": 3.05}, {"text": "and spray everything with hand sanitizer", "start": 62.13, "duration": 2.17}, {"text": "as part of their compulsion;", "start": 64.3, "duration": 1.53}, {"text": "Two:", "start": 66.16, "duration": 0.57}, {"text": "Obsession with symmetry or orderliness.", "start": 66.73, "duration": 2.4}, {"text": "This leads to excessive fear of oneself", "start": 69.64, "duration": 2.49}, {"text": "or his or her family getting hurt", "start": 72.13, "duration": 2.13}, {"text": "from things that are not in their place.", "start": 74.26, "duration": 2.34}, {"text": "So,", "start": 76.6, "duration": 0.7}, {"text": "they suffer compulsively tidies up everywhere,", "start": 77.3, "duration": 2.46}, {"text": "everytime.", "start": 79.76, "duration": 0.9}, {"text": "Even to the smallest thing.", "start": 80.66, "duration": 1.8}, {"text": "This person can also be obsessed", "start": 82.46, "duration": 2.04}, {"text": "and stressed out on things that are\nnot symmetrical or not in order.", "start": 84.5, "duration": 3.56}, {"text": "Three:", "start": 88.54, "duration": 0.56}, {"text": "Obsession to checking", "start": 89.1, "duration": 1.53}, {"text": "For example,", "start": 90.76, "duration": 0.8}, {"text": "you feel particularly scared", "start": 91.56, "duration": 1.42}, {"text": "that your car might get stolen anytime.", "start": 92.98, "duration": 2.12}, {"text": "So you keep checking it", "start": 95.1, "duration": 1.33}, {"text": "almost every second.", "start": 96.43, "duration": 1.27}, {"text": "Peaking out the window,", "start": 98.0, "duration": 1.13}, {"text": "and making sure your car is there.", "start": 99.13, "duration": 1.63}, {"text": "You also bring your car key all the time", "start": 100.94, "duration": 2.12}, {"text": "to repeatedly press the lock button.", "start": 103.06, "duration": 1.97}, {"text": "Four:", "start": 105.42, "duration": 0.64}, {"text": "Obsessive and intrusive thoughts", "start": 106.06, "duration": 2.2}, {"text": "The thoughts can vary wildly,", "start": 108.26, "duration": 1.67}, {"text": "such as fear of having done an unforgivable sin.", "start": 109.93, "duration": 3.33}, {"text": "or scrupulosity,", "start": 113.26, "duration": 1.3}, {"text": "myth-related,", "start": 114.56, "duration": 1.34}, {"text": "such as believing some color or number\ncan bring bad luck;", "start": 115.9, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and thoughts of doing violence-related actions.", "start": 118.9, "duration": 3.1}, {"text": "Signs and Symptoms", "start": 122.14, "duration": 1.62}, {"text": "Some of the signs that you need\nto look out on yourself", "start": 124.02, "duration": 2.61}, {"text": "or your loved ones are", "start": 126.63, "duration": 1.3}, {"text": "- Inability to sleep tightly", "start": 127.93, "duration": 1.9}, {"text": "because the obsession keeps waking one up", "start": 129.83, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the middle of the night.", "start": 131.83, "duration": 1.03}, {"text": "- Highly concerned about small things", "start": 133.06, "duration": 2.14}, {"text": "or easily angered by them.", "start": 135.2, "duration": 1.46}, {"text": "- Struggling in life", "start": 136.92, "duration": 1.44}, {"text": "The intrusive thoughts", "start": 138.52, "duration": 1.11}, {"text": "may severely impair one's social skills", "start": 139.63, "duration": 2.07}, {"text": "and career performance.", "start": 141.7, "duration": 1.36}, {"text": "The key sign is", "start": 143.22, "duration": 1.21}, {"text": "a person with OCD will spend a lot of time,", "start": 144.43, "duration": 2.6}, {"text": "about an hour per day,", "start": 147.2, "duration": 1.43}, {"text": "doing the compulsion and distress", "start": 148.63, "duration": 2.1}, {"text": "without having any pleasure at all.", "start": 150.73, "duration": 1.8}, {"text": "In another words,", "start": 152.78, "duration": 0.92}, {"text": "if a person just happens to love cleanliness", "start": 153.7, "duration": 2.36}, {"text": "or strive for perfection", "start": 156.06, "duration": 1.4}, {"text": "does not experience any problem\nin daily activities,", "start": 157.46, "duration": 3.04}, {"text": "and carries out that chores happily and proudly.", "start": 160.72, "duration": 2.38}, {"text": "then the person is not having OCD.", "start": 163.28, "duration": 2.32}, {"text": "In children,", "start": 165.6, "duration": 0.93}, {"text": "males are affected more commonly.", "start": 166.53, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "While in adults,", "start": 168.53, "duration": 0.97}, {"text": "females are affected at a slightly higher rate.", "start": 169.5, "duration": 2.8}, {"text": "An example of women-specific OCD", "start": 172.3, "duration": 2.4}, {"text": "is post-partum OCD.", "start": 174.7, "duration": 1.56}, {"text": "Scientists are still debating", "start": 177.06, "duration": 1.37}, {"text": "on how people can have OCD.", "start": 178.43, "duration": 1.7}, {"text": "Fortunately,", "start": 180.13, "duration": 1.17}, {"text": "treatments to relieve the condition\nare available.", "start": 181.3, "duration": 2.53}, {"text": "We will discuss those in the next part.", "start": 183.83, "duration": 2.0}]